{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"CanonicalCombiningClass","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Canonical combining classes are used by the ordering algorithm to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"determine if two sequences of combining marks should be considered","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"canonically equivalent (that is, identical in interpretation). Two","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"sequences are canonically equivalent if they are equal when sorting the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"scalars in ascending order by their combining class.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"For example, consider the sequence ","type":"text"},{"code":"\"\\u{0041}\\u{0301}\\u{0316}\"","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" (LATIN"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"CAPITAL LETTER A, COMBINING ACUTE ACCENT, COMBINING GRAVE ACCENT BELOW).","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The combining classes of these scalars have the numeric values 0, 230, and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"220, respectively. Sorting these scalars by their combining classes yields","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"\\u{0041}\\u{0316}\\u{0301}\""},{"text":", so two strings that differ only by the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"ordering of those scalars would compare as equal:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let aboveBeforeBelow = \"\\u{0041}\\u{0301}\\u{0316}\"","let belowBeforeAbove = \"\\u{0041}\\u{0316}\\u{0301}\"","print(aboveBeforeBelow == belowBeforeAbove)","\/\/ Prints \"true\""]},{"text":"Named and Unnamed Combining Classes","level":1,"type":"heading","anchor":"Named-and-Unnamed-Combining-Classes"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Canonical combining classes are defined in the Unicode Standard as","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"integers in the range ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"0...254"},{"text":". For convenience, the standard assigns","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"symbolic names to a subset of these combining classes.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CanonicalCombiningClass"},{"type":"text","text":" type conforms to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RawRepresentable"},{"type":"text","text":" with a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"raw value of type ","type":"text"},{"code":"UInt8","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". You can create instances of the type by using","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the static members named after the symbolic names, or by using the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"init(rawValue:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" initializer."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let overlayClass = Unicode.CanonicalCombiningClass(rawValue: 1)","let overlayClassIsOverlay = overlayClass == .overlay","\/\/ overlayClassIsOverlay == true"]}]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/Unicode\/CanonicalCombiningClass"},"metadata":{"title":"Unicode.CanonicalCombiningClass","role":"symbol","extendedModule":"Swift","roleHeading":"Structure","platforms":[{"deprecated":false,"name":"iOS","unavailable":false,"beta":false,"introducedAt":"8.0"},{"deprecated":false,"name":"iPadOS","unavailable":false,"beta":false,"introducedAt":"8.0"},{"deprecated":false,"introducedAt":"13.0","unavailable":false,"name":"Mac Catalyst","beta":false},{"unavailable":false,"beta":false,"introducedAt":"10.10